Public sector borrowing, wey be sey na di largest amount of Britain government deficit, or surplus, na im dem cut down compared to #200 million in September, compared to #765 million in August, and deficit of 1,08 billion in September 1988.

For di six months wey be sey dey start from April 1 to April 1, surplus of #500 million, compare with surplus of #3.6 billion for di year earlier period.

Government dey project a total of 14 billion surplus for di fiscal year.

Di report wey dey public sector, to borrow na receipt from di sale of state owned enterprises.

Concluding dat receipt, government go don add about $2.5 billion for di first six months compared to #1.3 billion a year ago.

